extra.enrollment_requirement:
Prerequisite    Permission of the Department
Exclusion    No more than 6.0 units from MATH120;121;122;123;124;126

basic.description:
Differentiation and integration of elementary functions, with applications to physical and social sciences.  Topics include limits, related rates, Taylor polynomials, and introductory techniques  and applications of integration.  
NOTE    Not intended for students pursuing a MATH or STAT plan.
basic.subject: MATH
basic.title: Differential and Integral Calculus I
